  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Strip the <strong>sage&nbsp;leaves</strong> from their <strong>stalks</strong> and chop the <strong>stalks</strong> finely&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Slice the<strong> portobello mushrooms</strong> finely</p>\r\n<p>Slice the <strong>chestnut mushrooms</strong> finely</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/986.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/986.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/986.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/986.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/986.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the<strong> sage leaves</strong> and cook them for 1 min or until they're crisp</p>\r\n<p>Once crisp, transfer them to a plate (keep the pan with the oil!) and season them lightly with&nbsp;<strong>salt</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/986.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/986.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/986.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/986.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/986.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a medium heat&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced&nbsp;</strong><strong>chestnut mushrooms</strong> and <strong>sliced</strong>&nbsp;<strong>portobello mushrooms</strong> with a big pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook them for 5-6 min or until the <strong>mushrooms</strong> have lightly browned</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/986.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/986.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/986.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/986.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/986.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>linguine</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Cook the <strong>linguine </strong>for 8-10 min or until it's cooked with a slight bite</p>\r\n<p>Once done reserve 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong>, then drain the<strong> linguine</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/986.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/986.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/986.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/986.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/986.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely dice the <strong>shallot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Peel and chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\r\n<p>Grate the<strong> Italian hard cheese</strong></p>\r\n<p>Crack the <strong>eggs&nbsp;</strong>into a shallow bowl and beat them with a fork</p>\r\n<p>Add 3/4 of the&nbsp;<strong>grated cheese</strong> and season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> - this is your<strong>&nbsp;cheesy egg mixture</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/986.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/986.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/986.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/986.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/986.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the mushrooms have browned, add the <strong>chopped shallot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>chopped sage stalks</strong> and a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and cook for a further 2-3 min or until the shallots have softened</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> to a large bowl</p>\r\n<p>Wash and dry the <strong>rocket</strong>, then add it to the bowl and mix - this is your <strong>rocket salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/986.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
